caption: We stopped and ate at Shorts Burgers while in Iowa City and we were really impressed with their food and service.  I ordered the Hardin chicken sandwich with fries and every bite was delicious!  Best natural cut fries I’ve ever had.

I miss Short's so much since moving away from Iowa.  I had a chance to stop by this last trip and had my favorite burger in the world: the Dundee.  Short's now gives you the choice of the number of burger patties you want.  I got a double and also splurge on that extra running egg.  Sourced from a nearby farm in Amana, the freshness of the meat used for the patties is what makes Short's burger so good.  I guess there has been a recent expansion out onto the actual street (N Clinton St.) for an addition of 4 tables.  Since I was driving, I didn't order the Millstream beer on tap.  This place can get quite busy, but the wait is well worth it.

Went into this restaurant for the first time with my family.  Place was small, waiting for a booth to open up was a bit of wait, but, it was a Saturday evening. The dining area was small, the place was packed and there was limited seating booths;  But, I found the atmosphere to be quite pleasant, and I liked the intimate feel of the place.  Our burgers were brought out to us, the fries were fantastic and the burger was delicious as everyone of my family members would agree.  Downfall of the place was that our waiter was busy, but it wasn't an excuse for the unsatisfactory service that we received from him.  We had to wait until he whizzed on by us for the tenth time  in order for us to stop him and ask him if we could get refills on our drinks. As the waiter had past by our table several times it was more than obvious that he noticed that our classes were empty for almost a complete hour since our drinks were first served to us,  and he did not once offer us a refill on our drinks.  We did not receive a refill until he past by us again and I had to stop him in his tracks just to receive a refill.  When dining out, you're not only paying for the food, but you're also paying for a standard of service which we did not receive in this restaurant.   The burger was very tasty, loved the garlic sauce for the fries and the same garlic sauce topped on the burgers, but my family and I were not satisfied with the soggy bun that got wet and fell apart in our  hands before we were even able to finish eating the burger.  I would have given this restaurant a 5 start rating very easily if it wasn't for the poor waiter service and the below standard burger bun.

We questioned who would go for two patties as the single patty burgers always left us stuffed. It wasn't until the burger came out that it was noticeably smaller, to the point where I could eat it with one hand. On top of that, the buns where hard and stale, making the burger taste different from what we have been having for years. All this being said, it left us disappointed and wondering if they are under new management. Hate to say it because it was the one of the best burgers in the state in my opinion, but the burgers are now tiny and at their prices ($9 for their basic burger) it will keep us from coming back.

We thought maybe it was just our bottle, so we tried a different one from another another table. Same problem. I asked the waitress if anyone had ever said anything, or if she could tell me what brand of ketchup they used. She gave me a blank stare, unsure. Her only comment was, “Maybe it tastes that way because it’s been sitting out all day?”  Seriously?! That’s disgusting and unsafe!! Unfortunately, this place disappointed me to the greatest degree possible. My roommates and I ordered burgers for carryout. I, being allergic to eggs, ordered a burger without any mayo or egg related product to avoid a possible reaction. Upon arriving home with the food we found that they had made the wrong burger for me. This one had mayo, which would have landed me in the hospital had I eaten it unknowingly. This sort of thing happens all the time in the food industry, so I wasn't too upset. We went back to the restaurant to see if we could get the order fixed and to my disappointment, they were not so cooperative. The bartender/manager proceeded to take the receipt out of my hand, and tell me that there was nothing he could do. At this point I was a little upset. I continued home and decided to give them a call, to see if I could straighten this out with someone else. Unfortunately, the man that turned me away was the one running the phones. After confirming that I was the one who came in to have this whole thing fixed, he said, and these are the exact words, "We advise our customers to look at the menu before ordering, so sorry we can't compensate for a customers mistake." and proceeded to hang up on me. This left a little bit of a sour taste in my mouth. After taking my money, and hanging up on me, I will surely never be giving this establishment my business ever again. To anyone in the downtown Iowa City area looking for a good burger, I would advise trying out Atlas or Quinton's. Both have astounding burgers, AND great service.

The service was laughably bad tonight. I’ve been here before, and it is has NEVER been this bad. The host seated people of our same group size before us whose names had obviously been taken after ours. A supposed 10-15 minute wait was then doubled. The server brought us our waters 10 minutes after we asked for them, forgot one, and never brought it. I asked for a water refill later and never got it. My companion was brought the wrong beer.
